  "text": "Awareness varied between 15% and 40% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [8] and the proportion who were treated varied between 14% and 82% [CITATION_3] [8] [CITATION_4] . Factors associated with better awareness or treatment included older age, being a woman, urban areas of residence and high body mass index (BMI). Control of treated hypertensive did not exceed 40% [8, [CITATION_5] .",
